Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
specifySpareGate(25.10)                                specifySpareGate(25.10)

Name
       specifySpareGate - Specifies spare gates to place

Syntax
       specifySpareGate

       {-help}

       {-cell <leafCellName>

          |-inst <instanceName>

          | -hinst {<hierarchicalInstanceName>}}

       Specifies spare gates to place. To localize spare gate placement, guide
       the  module containing the spare gate during the floorplanning session.
       This command should be used before placing the design.

Parameters
       -cell <leafCellName>
              Specifies the cell type names of the spare gate cells.  You  can
              use  this  parameter to specify leaf cells (standard cells)--you
              cannot use it to specify spare modules. You  can  use  wildcards
              with this parameter.

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each specifySpareGate parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man specifySpareGate.

       -hinst {<hierarchicalInstanceName>}
              Specifies a  hierarchical  instance  that  contains  spare  gate
              cells.  A  hierarchical instance acts as one unit (a submodule).
              The units are evenly spaced and are close together when they are
              distributed.

              You can use wildcards when specifying the hierarchical  instance
              names.

       -inst <instanceName>
              Specifies  the  leaf  instance names of the spare gates. You can
              use wildcards when specifying instance names.

Examples
              * The following command specifies all cell types YFD2S_SPG to be
                spare gates:

                specifySpareGate -cell YFD2S_SPG

              * The following command specifies instance SH16/I1022  to  be  a
                spare gate:

                specifySpareGate -inst SH16/I1022

              * The  following command specifies that all instances in SH16 to
                be spare gates:

                specifySpareGate -inst SH16/*

              * The following command treats all instances with the cell  type
                NAND2X1 as spare cells. If the design uses some of these cells
                as  spares  and some as not spare, use the -inst parameter in-
                stead.

                specifySpareGate -cell NAND2X1

              *

                The following example specifies multiple spare gates instances
                for the ECO placement:

                specifySpareGate -inst spare_lv_more_* specifySpareGate  -inst
                *SPAREcells_lv_*

                Note:  The  specifySpareGate does not accept the "list" option
                for defining multiple spare gates.

Related Information
              * Placing the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

                * Placing Spare Cells and Spare Modules

